Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.59,0:04:41.49,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's wrong, Kanamori?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.49,0:04:42.46,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,Are we in trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.86,0:04:50.06,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,There's so damn much I can poke holes \Nin here, I can't bring myself to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.06,0:04:53.55,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's bad. Because the \Ntwo of us can't exactly...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.07,0:05:05.49,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,Extracurricular activities are \Nconsidered a full-fledged part of education.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.49,0:05:09.47,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,The government curriculum details \Nas much, along with the rules involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.47,0:05:11.25,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,We're fully willing to consider \Nany directions you have,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.25,0:05:12.99,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,if they actually serve a purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.99,0:05:17.25,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's not very educational to use \Nclub activities to earn money, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.25,0:05:19.36,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't the culture festival a means of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.36,0:05:21.25,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,securing profits from \Noutside of the school, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.25,0:05:23.51,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,That's... a special exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.51,0:05:28.26,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,Look, here... "Athletic, \Ncultural, or technical pursuits
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.26,0:05:30.10,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,in order to exercise intellectual curiosity,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.10,0:05:32.32,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,cultivate a sense of responsibility, \Nand develop teamwork."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.32,0:05:33.89,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,That's what it says!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.89,0:05:38.03,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,We all saw your film. It was incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.03,0:05:40.21,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,Especially for high school students.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.21,0:05:42.45,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,So we think what you're doing is wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.45,0:05:45.51,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,But you can't try and profit off of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.51,0:05:48.62,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,That makes it something else \Nthan education. Don't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.62,0:05:55.02,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,You've been avoiding explaining why, \Nexactly, turning a profit isn't educational.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.02,0:05:57.07,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,I have not!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.07,0:06:00.67,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that, working diligently \Nwith your friends on something
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.67,0:06:03.95,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,can provide things money can't buy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.46,0:06:07.94,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starting to wonder if the \Ngovernment curriculum guidelines
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.94,0:06:10.26,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,say something about only \Nfools becoming teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.35,0:06:15.63,main,Dotonbori,0000,0000,0000,,How could you say that?! They're all \Ngreat people! I mean, they're teachers!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.63,0:06:19.49,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,I think you might have what it \Ntakes to be a teacher, president.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.49,0:06:20.95,main,Dotonbori,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You think?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.73,0:06:25.69,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get to the real issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.69,0:06:29.67,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,The bottom line is, a lot of people outside \Nthe school, including parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.67,0:06:33.13,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,aren't comfortable with students \Ngetting involved with money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.13,0:06:35.08,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,And schools don't cope well with pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.08,0:06:38.62,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,Which means they don't feel like \Nthe risk your little operation
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.62,0:06:41.77,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,might incur is worth the trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.77,0:06:44.84,main,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,There are a lot of political \Nconsiderations for a school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.84,0:06:45.99,top,Teacher A,0000,0000,0000,,To say nothing about the legal—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.32,0:06:47.20,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,What's the point of an educational institution
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.20,0:06:49.33,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,if it won't stand up for its students?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.88,0:06:51.61,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,People who don't understand business
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.61,0:06:55.27,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,will fall behind those who do,\N and be worse off for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.27,0:06:58.58,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Spewing out superficial pleasantries \Nabout "dreams" and "hard work,"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.58,0:07:01.37,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,while turning away from anything \Nthat might cause a headache.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.37,0:07:02.90,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Is that your idea of teaching?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.35,0:07:05.82,main,Teacher B,0000,0000,0000,,We just can't have you doing whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.82,0:07:08.17,main,Teacher B,0000,0000,0000,,The school has to consider its \Nrelationship with the town, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.17,0:07:11.01,main,Teacher B,0000,0000,0000,,What would you be using this money for, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.01,0:07:15.42,main,Teacher B,0000,0000,0000,,For all your talk about how this is \Nsome high-minded business exercise,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.42,0:07:20.19,main,Teacher B,0000,0000,0000,,aren't you just using the school's \Nname to benefit yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.19,0:07:22.26,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.26,0:07:26.42,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,I'll use anything that helps. \NCall it a "means to survive."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.42,0:07:28.18,main,Teacher B,0000,0000,0000,,You're all still students.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.18,0:07:31.25,main,Teacher B,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't there things your club \Ncould only be doing while you're still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.25,0:07:34.18,main,Teacher B,0000,0000,0000,,We all want you to cherish \Nthe time you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.18,0:07:36.43,main,Teacher B,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to rush into adulthood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.43,0:07:38.34,main,Teacher B,0000,0000,0000,,Because once you've grown up, you'll have to—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.26,0:07:39.10,top,K,0000,0000,0000,,Too optimistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.10,0:07:41.19,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,"The effort itself was the reward."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.19,0:07:42.25,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,It's an extracurricular cliche,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.25,0:07:45.44,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,and people who indulge in it learn \Nthe hard truth when they're adults.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.44,0:07:50.93,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, we didn't ask the chamber \Nof commerce to fund the production,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.93,0:07:53.50,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,we proposed a joint operation with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.50,0:07:55.95,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,And they decided to accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.87,0:07:58.18,main,Teacher B,0000,0000,0000,,I think we're done here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.18,0:08:00.61,main,Teacher B,0000,0000,0000,,The point is, you're free \Nto participate in the event,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.61,0:08:01.96,main,Teacher B,0000,0000,0000,,but you can't accept any money earned at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.96,0:08:03.46,main,Teacher B,0000,0000,0000,,Understood?
