Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.38,0:15:13.77,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,It was once a luxurious home to wealthy tenants!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.77,0:15:19.43,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,And inside the clock, high atop it,\N a massive treasure is hidden!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.43,0:15:20.35,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Thus...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.35,0:15:29.59,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,An alliance of thieves has targeted it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.86,0:15:36.70,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,They face...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.70,0:15:39.09,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,The bodyguard hired by the building's owners.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.97,0:15:42.00,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,So a security guard, basically.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.00,0:15:44.75,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,The last scene is a duel atop the \Ngrass field that grows on the roof...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.90,0:15:47.88,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Stop. Hold it right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.88,0:15:50.09,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,This is one huge clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.09,0:15:53.53,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,How about that concept? It'd make \Nfor a great 15-minute short!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.53,0:15:57.89,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Stop talking about other projects. \NFocus on finishing the one you're working on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.14,0:16:01.20,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.14,0:16:03.14,sign_23021_353_K_,Signs,0000,0000,0000,,K
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.20,0:16:03.14,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,There are Ks!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.14,0:16:04.96,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,K? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.96,0:16:07.97,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,You take the "K" from "kinetic \Nenergy" and call it a "K-cannon!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.96,0:16:22.66,sign_23021_353_K_,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,K
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.97,0:16:11.74,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's a DEW the Imperial Army \Nwas cooking up in secret...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.74,0:16:14.19,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,A {\b1}D{\b0}irected-{\b1}E{\b0}nergy {\b1}W{\b0}eapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.19,0:16:15.93,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Those are urban legends, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.93,0:16:18.77,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,But then, it turns out, they're real!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.77,0:16:22.68,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,And maybe this is the forgotten \Nlaboratory where it was worked on!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.68,0:16:23.81,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Gonna stop you right there again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.81,0:16:25.88,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Get back on topic with our current project.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.88,0:16:27.58,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,I feel a guiding hand here...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.58,0:16:31.86,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,This time, we're working something \Nwe were destined to make!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.89,0:16:37.80,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Essentially...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.80,0:16:41.25,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,In our club room, on the \Nother side of the coast,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.25,0:16:43.85,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,the subject for an exposure \Ntest was being stored.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.79,0:16:46.86,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Something was fired from this side...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.86,0:16:49.86,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Which lit something in the eizouken club room
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.86,0:16:54.36,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,that kicked those fans we have \Ninto gear, to awaken something!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.36,0:16:56.82,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,Asakusa's gone crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.36,0:16:59.66,sign_23021_353_K_,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,K
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.82,0:16:59.66,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,I just figured out the \Nconnection to my storyboards!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.66,0:17:03.15,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,A mecha to fight those UFOs was\N developed right where we stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.15,0:17:06.42,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, this was the base \Nfor the Shibahama military!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.42,0:17:08.35,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds good to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.35,0:17:12.32,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,See, Kanamori? This bit of sound \Nhunting paid fine dividends!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.32,0:17:13.84,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Crap, my target!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.84,0:17:16.20,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody, gimme a hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.84,0:17:22.85,sign_23021_353_K_,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(400,20)}K
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.20,0:17:19.19,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Kanamori, get the fluffy thing from my bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.19,0:17:21.04,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Asakusa, set up the tripod!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.04,0:17:22.26,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Roger Wilco!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.33,0:17:26.34,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Is this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.34,0:17:28.41,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusaki, your jacket's kinda noisy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.41,0:17:29.37,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.81,0:17:40.91,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Almost time. Nobody move a muscle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.19,0:18:15.03,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Good work, everyone. That went smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.38,0:18:18.66,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,That was nerve-wracking!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.66,0:18:20.43,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,I finally got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.03,0:18:23.53,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised you didn't have it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.03,0:18:35.55,sign_23021_353_K_,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(400,20)}K
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.53,0:18:25.53,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,There's an old one in the club's collection,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.53,0:18:28.67,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,but the sound has degraded with time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.67,0:18:33.40,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,But even though everything else is \Nin ruins, this bell still rings out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.40,0:18:35.55,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably just been forgotten about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.19,0:18:38.55,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,It continues to ring for some reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.09,0:18:43.56,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,That's magnificent!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.54,0:18:45.62,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,All right,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.62,0:18:49.35,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,the bell that continues to chime for \Nsome reason has given me a new idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.35,0:18:50.56,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough out of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.42,0:19:07.61,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna go next!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.61,0:19:09.55,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, eizouken.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.08,0:19:11.54,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,The class president!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.54,0:19:14.67,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, no. I'm actually the secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.33,0:19:19.76,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,So, did you figure out what to \Ndo about that stuff from before?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.76,0:19:22.93,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,The copyrights of works belong \Nto their individual creators.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.93,0:19:26.10,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,We'll enter Comet A as the film club,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.10,0:19:30.02,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,and then any sales and collection of \Ncash will be done on an individual basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.79,0:19:32.90,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you just enter a contest?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.90,0:19:35.69,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,A contest would be good for our reputation,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.69,0:19:37.40,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,but it'd take too long to pay dividends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.40,0:19:41.22,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,An event like this gets us instant \Nrecognition, an influx of income,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.22,0:19:43.63,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,and market research, all in one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.59,0:19:49.54,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,The eizouken's agenda is production \Nand research, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.54,0:19:52.61,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Management is a type of research, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.61,0:19:54.47,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,The baseball club does that kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.47,0:19:59.84,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,They keep records of their sales, \Norganize the data, and then report on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.84,0:20:01.71,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural that popularity
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.71,0:20:06.15,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,would be the standard by which \Nclub activities are measured.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.15,0:20:08.49,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,You could manage all that inside \Nthe school's jurisdiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.49,0:20:11.30,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be anything more \Nthan a simulation, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.30,0:20:14.62,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's not exactly a model for society.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.62,0:20:16.91,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,Schools are a world unto themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.91,0:20:19.94,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,Step too far outside of that world, \Nand you won't be protected anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.89,0:20:22.90,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,What're you getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.67,0:20:25.91,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Behold!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.69,0:20:30.83,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,We're moving beyond simple rotation!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.71,0:20:32.97,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Fans, drills...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.97,0:20:36.69,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,propeller skirts, ducted fans, and chainsaws!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.18,0:20:40.33,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's time we reconsider all \Nof these spinning machines!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.33,0:20:40.96,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,What is this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.35,0:20:42.63,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Her job.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.63,0:20:43.77,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,This?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.93,0:20:46.85,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,This motion is more like a gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.85,0:20:48.47,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,Like in a clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.46,0:20:54.67,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,What is this? Wavy grass?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.67,0:20:57.55,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's wavy sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.65,0:21:03.19,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,You layer it like this, the \Nsame way you would an image.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.75,0:21:06.20,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.01,0:21:12.19,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,You knock it around, layer it, \Nclip it up, and reattach it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.99,0:21:14.61,main,Sakaki,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of tool is it supposed to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.21,0:21:16.55,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'll think that up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.47,0:21:30.05,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.02,0:21:33.97,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,This equipment is said to be able \Nto transmit wishes and gratitude
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.97,0:21:36.99,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,from the surface world to the underwater one!
